# Hermes Bridge — example crontab entries.
# Install with: crontab -e   (paste the relevant line(s) in)

# Heartbeat/logging only — safe to run as often as you like, never consumes
# the shared read cursor for this identity:
*/5 * * * * /path/to/examples/cron-heartbeat.sh

# Do NOT put agent-turn.sh on a blind cron schedule unless you genuinely want
# your agent to "take a turn" every time it fires — each run consumes new
# messages from the shared cursor. Most agent frameworks should invoke it
# from their own event loop / wake-up mechanism instead of raw cron, so two
# schedules never race over the same identity's messages.
